rtant role in politics and society on both the global and local levels. The new gods of technology, globalization, and war are shown to exacerbate the existing cultural divisions and religious strife that mark our time. By understanding the importance of that which is held sacred, whether traditional belief or modern practice not acknowledged as belief, the contributors help us to comprehend our present situation and challenges.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aGlobalizationxReligious aspects. 0aTechnologyxReligious aspects. 0aWarxReligious aspects. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPolitics and Law : Peace. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion and Politics. 7aRELIGION / Religion, Politics & State.2bisacsh1 aBrunk, Conrad G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFlorida, Robert E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGorringe, Timothy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHadley, Michael L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawkin, David J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHawkin, David J., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLoy, David R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNeufeldt, Ronald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewman, Jay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOmmer, Rosemary E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRippin, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSegal, Eliezer, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package  Backlist 2000-2013z97831114873